<b>Welcome to this study about decision making.</b><br><br>

The experiment lasts approximately 30 minutes. You will be asked to do some or all of the following things in the experiment: <br>
1) Look at visual displays, like pictures of real or nonsense objects, real or nonsense words or complex visual scenes. These may include fearful/sad/disgusted/happy/surprised faces and scenes (e.g. spiders, war zones).<br>
2) Listen to sounds including words, sentences, and/or familiar or unfamiliar non-verbal sounds;<br>
3) Name or describe pictures, words or sounds, either silently, "in your head", or out loud;<br>
4) Imagine different kinds of life events occurring to you, sounds or actions;<br>
5) Make choices between different items presented to you<br>
6) Move your hands and fingers in different kinds of simple patterns and/or to indicate a response to onscreen stimuli when prompted.<br>
7) Give a presentation in front of others.<br><br>

This study has been approved by the UCL Research Ethics Committee as Project ID Number: 3990/003<br><br>

